45:33.840 --> 45:40.880
the Silicon Valley, Valley Bank issue, it's not so much their issue as much as a worldwide issue.

45:41.120 --> 45:53.600
What happened is that what's a bank? A bank takes in deposits, and then it takes that money and it

45:53.600 --> 46:01.440
invests it in things. And so they bought a lot of government bonds that had a higher yield than

46:01.440 --> 46:08.400
they were paying out in the deposits. There's a tightness of monetary policy, and those yields

46:08.400 --> 46:16.720
went up and the bonds went down in value. And then the amount they have to pay out went up in value.

46:17.440 --> 46:26.400
And so they went broke. And that is happening all over. That happens not only through banks.

46:26.400 --> 46:33.760
Banks as a whole did a lot of that. But insurance companies and so on, all around the world,

46:33.840 --> 46:38.240
same sort of thing happened in Europe. Same sort of thing happened with Japanese

46:39.280 --> 46:49.440
companies even buying US dollar bonds a lot. And so if you were to mark those to market,

46:50.400 --> 46:59.920
you would have a terrible calamity. But what's going to likely happen is they don't want any

46:59.920 --> 47:07.440
